    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="169"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.6135/108</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Cuban Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Márquez Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-12">February 12,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform Your Excellency
                    that my Government has instructed me to transmit its expression of gratitude <pb
                        facs="0249" n="183" xml:id="pg_183"/> for the part of the message of
                    President Roosevelt to the United States Congress regarding sugar,<note n="76"
                        xml:id="d169fn76">See <hi rend="italic">Congressional Record</hi>, vol. 78,
                        pt. 2, p. 2176.</note> with relation to Cuba. This message has conveyed to
                    the distressed people of Cuba the hopes of a prosperous future.</p>
                <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M. <hi rend="smallcaps">Márquez Sterling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
